I'm not the biggest fan of this, but it's pretty solid in the right deck. I don't really like that it asks you to end your turn in no stance, which can have disastrous consequences going into your next turn, as so many champ cards rely on being in a stance to get their full effects (berserker/defensive combo cards, finishers). To be fair, drawing that extra card makes it more likely that you can re-enter a stance, and you can always just draft more stance entry cards to compensate. You will also want to draft additional finishers in order to more reliably get out of a stance to trigger this. You would have to put in an awful lot of work to turn this into ring of the serpent, which is fair when you consider that it's only a common relic. It's sort of similar to <art of war>, another common relic that can imitate a boss relic if you really build around it, and can also just provide some reasonable value every once in a while. 

I will say that card draw is pretty valuable on champ, largely due to it's scarcity, so building around this can be quite useful to cover that weakness. Runic pyramid deserves special note, as that can make it much easier to hold onto finishers and stance entry cards so that you are consistently proccing the bonus without taking the downside of not being able to enter a stance next turn. This relic gets better as you head towards late game and getting through your deck quickly to find your scaling/draw past enemy curses becomes more important, and I would consider buying it more if I was near the end of the run rather than towards the beginning. Pairs well with moment of truth so that you can hold onto a finisher for the turn before you really want to trigger this draw effect. Arena preparation can also help, as the skills it makes will have retain, and can be finishers/stance entry cards.
